 "text": "Laos: an element of the North Vietnamese 324th Division, normally located in the Vinh area, was as of 22 January engaged in improving the road (Route 7) between the North Vietnamese border and Ban Ban in the Plaines des Jarres area.\nthis road is now open to truck traffic. The road could become a main Communist supply route to the Plaines des Jarres area but a major effort would be required to keep it passable during the rainy season which commences in about two months.\n\nHanoi on 7 February broadcast a recent interview with Kong Le in which he expressed his thanks for aid from \"the Soviet Union and other socialist countries.\" This is the second recent public reference to Soviet assistance for pro-Communist forces in Laos. On 2 February, Chen Yi, Communist China's foreign minister, commented that Soviet \"support\" was a \"righteous action.\" Chen Yi's remark may have been intended to justify his own offer of Chinese Communist support—\"if the lawful government of Laos headed by Souvanna Phouma\" asks for it", "token_count": 173, "token_end_0based": 180, "token_start_0based": 8, "token_text": "laos an element of the north vietnamese 324th division normally located in the vinh area was as of 22 january engaged in improving the road route 7 between the north vietnamese border and ban ban in the plaines des jarres area this road is now open to truck traffic the road could become a main communist supply route to the plaines des jarres area but a major effort would be required to keep it passable during the rainy season which commences in about two months hanoi on 7 february broadcast a recent interview with kong le in which he expressed his thanks for aid from the soviet union and other socialist countries this is the second recent public reference to soviet assistance for pro-communist forces in laos on 2 february chen yi communist china's foreign minister commented that soviet support was a righteous action chen yi's remark may have been intended to justify his own offer of chinese communist support if the lawful government of laos headed by souvanna phouma asks for it", "unred_source_page": 5}
